We haven&#39;t implemented a general/better solution. I know that some
projects have (and are probably still) probing for whether a site
gives such &#39;soft 404s&#39; by requesting a random path URL on the host,
and seeing if a 200 comes back. Presumably they could also use the
content of that page as a hint to detect other &#39;soft 404s&#39; on the
site. (Though, many of these situations are caused by scripts that
affect only part of the URL space, not the whole site.)

Let us know if you come up with anything good!

- Gordon @ IA

